# Page route rules

Pages are **composition roots**, not feature implementations.

## Do in `page.tsx`

- Parse `params` / `searchParams`
- Call `lib/` data functions or fetch APIs
- Set metadata (`generateMetadata`) when needed
- Render `<main>` wrapper + import feature components
- JSON-LD / SEO scripts (small inline blocks only)

## Do NOT in `page.tsx`

- Large JSX trees or repeated markup
- Client state (`useState`, `useEffect`)
- Form handling, modals, or interactive UI
- Utility functions — move to `lib/`
- Reusable UI — move to `components/<feature>/`

## Example (doctors route)

```tsx
import { DoctorsHero } from "@/components/doctors/DoctorsHero"
import { DoctorsList } from "@/components/doctors/DoctorsList"
import { getDoctors } from "@/lib/doctors-data"

export default async function Page({ params }: PageProps) {
  const { slug } = await params
  const doctors = getDoctors(slug?.[0] ?? "", slug?.[1] ?? "")

  return (
    <main className="bg-white min-h-screen">
      <div className="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-6 space-y-4">
        <DoctorsHero city={slug?.[0] ?? ""} speciality={slug?.[1] ?? ""} />
        <DoctorsList doctors={doctors} />
      </div>
    </main>
  )
}
```
